==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faucet
<hw>Fau"cet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fausset</ets>, perh. fr. L. <ets>fauces</ets> throat.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A fixture for drawing a liquid, as water, molasses,
oil, etc., from a pipe, cask, or other vessel, in such quantities as may
be desired; -- called also <altname>tap</altname>, and
<altname>cock</altname>. It consists of a tubular spout, stopped with a
movable plug, spigot, valve, or slide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The enlarged end of a section of pipe which receives
the spigot end of the next section.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fauchion</ent>⟦br⟧
